# {{ project_name }}

A full-stack starter generated by [claude-kit](https://github.com/ajyadav013/claude-kit):
a **{{ backend_label }}** backend and a **{{ frontend_label }}** frontend, wired together with a
**{{ db }}** database — and an autonomous SDLC (agents, rules, quality gates) baked in so you can
build features with Claude Code from day one.

## Quick start

### Option A — Docker (no local toolchains needed)

```bash
docker compose up --build
```

- Frontend: http://localhost:{{ web_port }}
- API + docs: http://localhost:{{ api_port }} (Swagger UI at `/docs`)
- The backend applies database migrations automatically on startup.

Stop with `docker compose down` (or `make down`).

### Option B — Local dev

Requires Python 3.11+ and Node 22+, plus a running {{ db }} (the compose `db` service works).

```bash
make setup          # backend venv + install, frontend npm install
make migrate        # apply backend migrations
# then, in two terminals:
cd backend && .venv/bin/uvicorn app.main:app --reload
cd frontend && npm run dev
```

## What's inside

```
{{ project_slug }}/
├── backend/            {{ backend_label }} — layered: router → service → repository → model
├── frontend/           {{ frontend_label }} — typed API client + feature folders
├── docker-compose.yml  db + backend + frontend
├── Makefile            common tasks (make help)
├── CLAUDE.md           engineering rules for Claude Code (tuned to this stack)
└── .claude/            agents, rules, skills, hooks, working memory
```

The example resource is **items**: a complete vertical slice (DB model → API → typed UI → tests)
you can copy as the pattern for new features.

## Common commands

| Task | Docker | Local |
|------|--------|-------|
| Start everything | `make up` | see Option B |
| Stop | `make down` | — |
| Backend tests | — | `cd backend && .venv/bin/pytest` |
| Frontend tests | — | `cd frontend && npm run test` |
| Lint + types (both) | — | `make lint` |
| New migration | — | `cd backend && .venv/bin/alembic revision --autogenerate -m "msg"` |

## Using the Claude Code agents

This project ships with claude-kit's autonomous SDLC. Open the folder in
[Claude Code](https://www.claude.com/product/claude-code) and the rules in `CLAUDE.md` plus the
agents, skills, and hooks under `.claude/` load automatically.

**Run the full pipeline on a task:**

```text
/claude-kit:sdlc Add a "completed" boolean to items, expose it in the API, and show a checkbox in the UI
```

The **orchestrator** classifies the work, writes a spec, runs review → implementation → tests →
security through quality gates, and stops to ask you at decision points. Backend and frontend are
independent **lanes** that run in parallel and are reconciled at the API contract.

**Other entry points:**

- `/claude-kit:status` — show working memory (current phase, next steps) and what's installed.
- Invoke a single agent for a focused task (e.g. the `sdlc-code-reviewer` to review a diff, or the
  `unit-tester` to add tests) by asking Claude to use it by name.
- Stack conventions the agents follow live in `.claude/rules/{{ backend_overlay_rule }}` and
  `.claude/rules/{{ frontend_overlay_rule }}` — each includes a step-by-step "add a feature" recipe.

Two memory systems keep long runs reliable: `.claude/CONTINUITY.md` (working memory, re-read every
turn) and `.claude/agent-memory/` (durable learnings). See `CLAUDE.md` for the full workflow, and
[claude-kit's agent guide](https://github.com/ajyadav013/claude-kit/blob/main/docs/agents.md) for a
deeper tour of every agent.
